    results_detail: 'Recommended CRS+HIPEC for epithelioid MPeM with PCI <20 and adequate performance status, endorsing cisplatin-based HIPEC (≈200–250 mg/m² ± doxorubicin, 41–43 °C, 60–90 min); designated sarcomatoid histology a contraindication to CRS+HIPEC; mandated BAP1 testing (with germline counselling); and positioned pemetrexed–cisplatin and dual immunotherapy (nivolumab + ipilimumab) as systemic options, integrating checkpoint blockade into the treatment paradigm.',
    practice_change: 'Standardised MPeM management internationally, aligning surgical selection with molecular testing and modern systemic therapy. It embedded routine BAP1 testing, defined HIPEC parameters, excluded sarcomatoid disease from aggressive surgery, and encouraged immunotherapy use/trial enrolment, creating a common framework for comparing outcomes across centres.',
    criticisms: 'Expert-consensus document (level IV) based on largely retrospective evidence, given the rarity of MPeM and absence of randomised HIPEC trials. Specific HIPEC doses/durations rest on limited data. Rapid evolution of immunotherapy may quickly date systemic recommendations.',
